# --- Production / local hygiene ---

# Host-linked metadata can expose project IDs and account linkage in a clone or PR diff.
.vercel/

# Log files capture machine paths and transient errors; they clutter history and can leak context.
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# Avoid committing private keys unless your team only vendors public certs (these extensions usually mean secret material).
*.pem
*.p12
*.key

# Cache and reports are regenerated locally or in CI; tracking them bloats the repo and causes merge noise.
.turbo/
playwright-report/
test-results/
.eslintcache

# Foundry workflows conventionally put funded deployer secrets here; keep them off remotes by default.
contracts/.env
